# KRW-Watcher — Caddy reverse proxy for a self-hosted VPS (automatic HTTPS)
#
# Replace "your-domain.example" below with your real domain (DNS A/AAAA record
# must point at this VPS). Caddy then auto-provisions and renews a free
# Let's Encrypt TLS certificate for it — no manual cert steps needed.
#
# Run the KRW-Watcher app on localhost:8010 behind this proxy, e.g.:
#   - docker compose (see deploy/docker-compose.yml), or
#   - systemd service running:
#       uvicorn backend.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8010 --workers 1
#     (SINGLE WORKER ONLY — the app holds in-memory state + an APScheduler.)
#
# Because the app sits behind this proxy, set ALLOWED_IPS=* in its env so the
# read endpoints stay reachable. Caddy automatically sets X-Forwarded-For /
# X-Forwarded-Proto, which the app already trusts to recover the real client IP.
# (Write endpoints — /api/cycle, /api/briefing/generate, /api/admin/*,
#  /admin-secure-panel/* — still require admin login or X-Cron-Secret.)

your-domain.example {
    encode gzip
    reverse_proxy localhost:8010
}
